## Bead noscope-5wl: Complete

**Commit:** `c6482dc` — `feat: standalone mint and revoke subcommands (noscope-5wl)`

### What was implemented

New module `src/mint.rs` with:

| Type/Function | Purpose | Rule |
|---|---|---|
| `MintEnvelope` | JSON output envelope with 5 fields for stdout | NS-060 |
| `MintEnvelope::from_scoped_token()` | Bridge from existing `ScopedToken` | NS-060 |
| `MintEnvelope::to_json()` | Raw token in stdout JSON (NS-064 exception) | NS-064 |
| `MintEnvelope::to_log_string()` | Redacted form for stderr/logs | NS-064 |
| `RevokeInput` | Revoke via `--token-id`+`--provider` or mint JSON | NS-061 |
| `validate_revoke_args()` | Rejects `--token` and `--token=value` (NS-012) | NS-061 |
| `validate_mint_args()` | Mandatory non-zero TTL, provider(s), role | NS-062 |
| `format_mint_output()` | JSON array or empty string (atomic) | NS-063 |
| `check_stdout_not_terminal()` | Exit 64 if isatty unless `--force` | NS-065 |
| `MintError` | Error type with exit codes and Display | All |

### Security hardening from Linus review
- `MintEnvelope` zeroizes token on `Drop` (NS-019 consistency)
- `Debug` impl redacts token field (NS-005 defense-in-depth)
- Not `Clone` (prevents careless duplication)
- `validate_revoke_args` catches `--token=value` combined form

### Test coverage
- **47 tests total**: 35 rule-specific + 12 edge cases from review
- All 245 tests pass across the full codebase
- Zero clippy warnings
